                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On March 26, 1953, during the course of the visit by French Prime Minister Mayer
                    to the United States, the French Delegation discussed with Secretary of State
                    Dulles, Secretary of the Treasury Humphrey, Director of Mutual Security Stassen,
                    and Assistant Secretary of Defense Nash the future role of France in the Western
                    trade control effort. For a brief description of this discussion, see telegram
                    5001 to Paris, March 27, in <ref target="frus1952-54v06p1">volume VI</ref>.</p>
            </div>
